Subject: [PATCH] C-6 pivot: enable a purecap Zero (C++ interpreter) build variant

Strategic pivot probe (per user direction): instead of hand-fixing each
cap-strip bug in HotSpot's runtime-emitted template interpreter (the
L0-L60 cascade), build the Zero variant, whose bytecode interpreter is
plain C++ (share/interpreter/zero/bytecodeInterpreter.cpp, ~3400 lines)
compiled by the Morello clang -> cap-correct by construction. Every oop
load becomes a clang-emitted capability load, so the CHERI load barrier
is automatic.

Changes to make a purecap Zero link & boot:
- os_cpu/bsd_zero/atomic_bsd_zero.hpp: Zero's per-size Atomic
  specializations stop at 8 bytes; add the 16-byte (capability-sized)
  PlatformCmpxchg/Xchg/Load/Store/Add used for oop CAS/xchg/load/store/
  bump on purecap (oop/Klass* are 16-byte caps). clang lowers __atomic_*
  on a 16-byte capability to the Morello cap atomics, preserving the tag.
- share/runtime/init.cpp, thread.cpp: guard the template-interpreter-only
  cap seeding (_cap_dispatch = Interpreter::dispatch_table(), the aarch64
  cap_data_table_base()) with !defined(ZERO) — ZeroInterpreter has no
  dispatch_table and the aarch64 cap_data/trampoline TUs aren't built for
  zero; null those fields in the zero branch.
- Build dep: Zero needs libffi; a purecap libffi (pkg64c libffi-3.4.4) was
  staged into the morello sysroot (sysroot side-artifact, not in this patch).

RESULT (java -version, Zero, -UseEpsilonGC -UseCompressed{Oops,ClassPointers}):
boots through init_globals, management, bytecodes, classLoader, codeCache,
VM_Version, stubRoutines, **Genesis (universe_init)**, gc_barrier_stubs,
interpreter_init_stub, accessFlags, InterfaceSupport, VMRegImpl::set_regName
-- i.e. it sails past the entire template-interpreter cascade that took
this session's L54-L60. Next fault is a SIGPROT in SharedRuntime::
generate_stubs (a far shorter, different list than the interpreter).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_zero/atomic_bsd_zero.hpp b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_zero/atomic_bsd_zero.hpp
index b9ee395bc30..4dab6e4c24c 100644
--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_zero/atomic_bsd_zero.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_zero/atomic_bsd_zero.hpp
@@ -203,6 +203,21 @@ inline D Atomic::PlatformAdd<8>::add_and_fetch(D volatile* dest, I add_value,
   return res;
 }
 
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI purecap: cap-sized (16-byte) atomic add — e.g. an atomically bumped
+// pointer/counter declared as intptr_t/__uintcap_t. clang's __atomic_add_fetch
+// on a capability adds to its address while preserving tag/bounds.
+template<>
+template<typename D, typename I>
+inline D Atomic::PlatformAdd<16>::add_and_fetch(D volatile* dest, I add_value,
+                                                atomic_memory_order order) const {
+  STATIC_ASSERT(16 == sizeof(D));
+  D res = __atomic_add_fetch(dest, add_value, __ATOMIC_RELEASE);
+  FULL_MEM_BARRIER;
+  return res;
+}
+#endif // __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+
 template<>
 template<typename T>
 inline T Atomic::PlatformXchg<4>::operator()(T volatile* dest,
@@ -302,4 +317,55 @@ inline void Atomic::PlatformStore<8>::operator()(T volatile* dest,
   os::atomic_copy64(reinterpret_cast<const volatile int64_t*>(&store_value), reinterpret_cast<volatile int64_t*>(dest));
 }
 
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI purecap: oop / Klass* are 16-byte capabilities, so the GC needs
+// cap-sized (16-byte) atomics. Zero's per-size specializations stop at 8;
+// add the 16-byte forms. clang lowers __atomic_* on a 16-byte capability
+// type to the Morello capability atomic instructions, preserving the tag.
+template<>
+template<typename T>
+inline T Atomic::PlatformCmpxchg<16>::operator()(T volatile* dest,
+                                                 T compare_value,
+                                                 T exchange_value,
+                                                 atomic_memory_order order) const {
+  STATIC_ASSERT(16 == sizeof(T));
+  T value = compare_value;
+  FULL_MEM_BARRIER;
+  __atomic_compare_exchange(dest, &value, &exchange_value, /*weak*/false,
+                            __ATOMIC_RELAXED, __ATOMIC_RELAXED);
+  FULL_MEM_BARRIER;
+  return value;
+}
+
+template<>
+template<typename T>
+inline T Atomic::PlatformXchg<16>::operator()(T volatile* dest,
+                                              T exchange_value,
+                                              atomic_memory_order order) const {
+  STATIC_ASSERT(16 == sizeof(T));
+  T result;
+  FULL_MEM_BARRIER;
+  __atomic_exchange(dest, &exchange_value, &result, __ATOMIC_RELAXED);
+  FULL_MEM_BARRIER;
+  return result;
+}
+
+template<>
+template<typename T>
+inline T Atomic::PlatformLoad<16>::operator()(T const volatile* src) const {
+  STATIC_ASSERT(16 == sizeof(T));
+  T value;
+  __atomic_load(const_cast<T*>(src), &value, __ATOMIC_RELAXED);
+  return value;
+}
+
+template<>
+template<typename T>
+inline void Atomic::PlatformStore<16>::operator()(T volatile* dest,
+                                                  T store_value) const {
+  STATIC_ASSERT(16 == sizeof(T));
+  __atomic_store(dest, &store_value, __ATOMIC_RELAXED);
+}
+#endif // __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+
 #endif // OS_CPU_BSD_ZERO_ATOMIC_BSD_ZERO_HPP
